spec: ab2881
version: ">=3.9"
error_model: python_exceptions
provenance:
  derived_from: [abc source, Python docs, https://docs.python.org/3/library/abc.html]
  not_derived_from: [abc_extra2866.zspec.zsdl — covers __rand__/__ror__/__rxor__ dict-presence, abc_extra2851.zspec.zsdl — covers __rlshift__/__rrshift__/__rpow__ dict-presence, abc_extra2836.zspec.zsdl — covers __rtruediv__/__rfloordiv__/__rmod__ dict-presence, any external dataset]
  notes: [Wave 639 theme — __iadd__/__isub__/__imul__ dict-presence checks for abc module types. In-place augmented assignment operators. ABC/ABCMeta/abstractmethod/abstractclassmethod/abstractstaticmethod are abstract base class infrastructure not numeric/sequence types — none define these dunders. abstractproperty excluded per campaign rules for 3.13+ removal. abstractclassmethod and abstractstaticmethod are deprecated but still present in Python 3.14.4. type(abc.abstractmethod(lambda: None)) yields function whose __dict__ also lacks these dunders. All expected values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0 2026-04-13.]
  created_at: "2026-04-13"

